    {
      "name": "Create Manual Attendance",
      "request": {
        "description": "Create or backfill attendance as HR.\n\nIf check-out extends past the configured work end time, the backend stores that extra time as `overtimeMinutes`, and `workedMinutes` excludes the configured break window.\n\nSample success response excerpt:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Attendance created successfully.\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"workedMinutes\": 480,\n    \"lateMinutes\": 0,\n    \"earlyLeaveMinutes\": 0,\n    \"overtimeMinutes\": 15,\n    \"status\": \"present\",\n    \"source\": \"manual\"\n  }\n}",
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"employee_id\": {{employee_id}},\n  \"attendance_date\": \"2026-04-03\",\n  \"check_in_time\": \"2026-04-03T08:15:00+07:00\",\n  \"check_out_time\": \"2026-04-03T17:15:00+07:00\",\n  \"notes\": \"Created by HR for late kiosk sync.\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/attendance/manual",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "attendance",
                "manual"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Outage Recovery Preview",
          "request": {
            "description": "Preview the default-selected employees for downtime recovery. The backend includes active employees who are not on approved leave and do not already have attendance for the selected date.\n\nSupports:\n- `search`\n- `department_id`\n- `per_page`\n\nSample response excerpt:\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"date\": \"2026-04-06\",\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"checkInAt\": \"2026-04-06T08:00:00+07:00\",\n      \"checkOutAt\": \"2026-04-06T17:00:00+07:00\",\n      \"notes\": \"System outage recovery\"\n    },\n    \"selectedEmployees\": {\n      \"current_page\": 1,\n      \"data\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": 7,\n          \"employeeCode\": \"EMP000007\",\n          \"name\": \"Emma Employee\",\n          \"department\": \"Operations\",\n          \"currentPosition\": \"Coordinator\",\n          \"selected\": true,\n          \"skipReason\": null\n        }\n      ],\n      \"per_page\": 10,\n      \"total\": 1\n    },\n    \"skipped\": {\n      \"counts\": {\n        \"onLeave\": 0,\n        \"existingAttendance\": 0\n      },\n      \"onLeave\": [],\n      \"existingAttendance\": []\n    }\n  }\n}",
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/attendance/outage-recovery/preview?date=2026-04-06&search=Emma&department_id={{department_id}}&per_page=10",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "attendance",
                "outage-recovery",
                "preview"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "date",
                  "value": "2026-04-06"
                },
                {
                  "key": "search",
                  "value": "Emma"
                },
                {
                  "key": "department_id",
                  "value": "{{department_id}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "per_page",
                  "value": "10"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Outage Recovery Apply",
          "request": {
            "description": "Create downtime recovery attendance only for the HR-confirmed employee list.\n\nIf `check_in_time` is provided and `check_out_time` is `null`, the backend creates an open attendance record so the employee can check out later by self-service or scan.\n\nIf both times are omitted, the backend uses the configured work start and end time for a full-day recovery record.\n\nSample success response excerpt:\n{\n  \"message\": \"Outage recovery attendance created successfully.\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"date\": \"2026-04-06\",\n    \"createdCount\": 2,\n    \"notes\": \"System outage recovery\",\n    \"employees\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": 7,\n        \"employeeCode\": \"EMP000007\",\n        \"name\": \"Emma Employee\",\n        \"department\": \"Operations\",\n        \"currentPosition\": \"Coordinator\",\n        \"selected\": true,\n        \"skipReason\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}",
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-06\",\n  \"employee_ids\": [{{employee_id}}],\n  \"check_in_time\": \"2026-04-06T09:15:00+07:00\",\n  \"check_out_time\": null,\n  \"notes\": \"System outage recovery\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/attendance/outage-recovery/apply",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "attendance",
                "outage-recovery",
                "apply"
              ]
            }
          }
